{
  "stem": "24814.3",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I've seen every kind of starvation and malnutrition, as a result of a disease primarily.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I've never seen anything like these people.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Again, they were so thin that the faces looked like bird's faces, the bones projected.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The arms were just bones, barely covered.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "The knees, the joints, were protuberant.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "The leg would be tiny and thin, and then there'd be a great big ball socket of the joint, and then tiny, thin, little rail of bone going up above it.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I couldn't understand quite how they even stood, the poor people, or how they could move, but they could do it.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I didn't have time for a lot of examination at Landsberg, the way I did at Dachau, because we-- we were in the combat elements, and on we went.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But our division rear people did a pretty good, credible job of cleaning it up, and getting the dead buried, and the living into hospitals, and getting food to everybody.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The young Jewish boy that I met first is the only one I remember vividly out of a sea of faces.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The one who told me his mother and father both had been burned, burned, burned.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he's the one that sticks in my mind, standing there clutching that, what was left of that loaf of bread, chewing on it, and crying as hard as he could cry.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Terrible sight.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "This was a simple work and death camp.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were put there to be starved and worked to death, is what they really were.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the killing was incidental.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "In other words, they saw the Allies approaching, and the orders were to kill them all.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "That's kind of camp it was.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon?",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Nothing like that.",
      "word_count": 3
    }
  ],
